explanation: The solution uses a hashmap to store the price at each timestamp and two heaps to keep track of the maximum and minimum prices. The `update` method updates the price at the given timestamp and pushes the new price to the heaps. The `current` method returns the price at the latest timestamp. The `maximum` and `minimum` methods return the maximum and minimum prices by checking the top of the heaps and removing any outdated prices.

